#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.95:0.2"
msgid "10. Saḷavagga "
msgstr "10. The Sixes "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 95. Mālukyaputtasutta → māluṅkyaputtasuttaṃ (bj) | saṃgayha 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.95:0.3"
msgid "95. Mālukyaputtasutta "
msgstr "95. Māluṅkyaputta "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.72, sc1
#. VAR: mālukyaputto → māluṅkyaputto (bj)
msgctxt "sn35.95:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā mālukyaputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mālukyaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Māluṅkyaputta went up to the Buddha … and asked him, "

msgctxt "sn35.95:1.2"
msgid "“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṃkhittena dhammaṃ desetu, yamahaṃ bhagavato dhammaṃ sutvā eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.95:2.1"
msgid "“Ettha dāni, mālukyaputta, kiṃ dahare bhikkhū vakkhāma. "
msgstr "“Well now, Māluṅkyaputta, what are we to say to the young monks, "

msgctxt "sn35.95:2.2"
msgid "Yatra hi nāma tvaṃ, bhikkhu, jiṇṇo vuddho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto saṅkhittena ovādaṃ yācasī”ti. "
msgstr "when even an old man like you, elderly and senior, advanced in years, having reached the final stage of life, asks the Realized One for brief advice?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.95:3.1"
msgid "“Kiñcāpāhaṃ, bhante, jiṇṇo vuddho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto. "
msgstr "“Sir, even though I’m an old man, elderly and senior, "

msgctxt "sn35.95:3.2"
msgid "Desetu me, bhante, bhagavā saṅkhittena dhammaṃ, desetu sugato saṅkhittena dhammaṃ, appeva nāmāhaṃ bhagavato bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājāneyyaṃ. Appeva nāmāhaṃ bhagavato bhāsitassa dāyādo assan”ti. "
msgstr "may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief! May the Holy one please teach me in brief! Hopefully I can understand the meaning of what the Buddha says. Hopefully I can be an heir of the Buddha’s teaching!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.95:4.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mālukyaputta, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Māluṅkyaputta? "

msgctxt "sn35.95:4.2"
msgid "ye te cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā adiṭṭhā adiṭṭhapubbā, na ca passasi, na ca te hoti passeyyanti? Atthi te tattha chando vā rāgo vā pemaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Do you have any desire or greed or fondness for sights known by the eye that you haven’t seen, you’ve never seen before, you don’t see, and you don’t think would be seen?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.95:4.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.95:5.1"
msgid "“Ye te sotaviññeyyā saddā assutā assutapubbā, na ca suṇāsi, na ca te hoti suṇeyyanti? Atthi te tattha chando vā rāgo vā pemaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“Do you have any desire or greed or affection for sounds known by the ear … "

msgctxt "sn35.95:5.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.95:6.1"
msgid "“Ye te ghānaviññeyyā gandhā aghāyitā aghāyitapubbā, na ca ghāyasi, na ca te hoti ghāyeyyanti? Atthi te tattha chando vā rāgo vā pemaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "smells known by the nose … "

msgctxt "sn35.95:6.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn35.95:7.1"
msgid "“Ye te jivhāviññeyyā rasā asāyitā asāyitapubbā, na ca sāyasi, na ca te hoti sāyeyyanti? Atthi te tattha chando vā rāgo vā pemaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "tastes known by the tongue … "

msgctxt "sn35.95:7.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn35.95:8.1"
msgid "“Ye te kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā asamphuṭṭhā asamphuṭṭhapubbā, na ca phusasi, na ca te hoti phuseyyanti? Atthi te tattha chando vā rāgo vā pemaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "touches known by the body … "

msgctxt "sn35.95:8.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.73, sc9
msgctxt "sn35.95:9.1"
msgid "“Ye te manoviññeyyā dhammā aviññātā aviññātapubbā, na ca vijānāsi, na ca te hoti vijāneyyanti? Atthi te tattha chando vā rāgo vā pemaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "thoughts known by the mind that you haven’t known, you’ve never known before, you don’t know, and you don’t think would be known?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.95:9.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn35.95:10.1"
msgid "“Ettha ca te, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhasutamutaviññātabbesu dhammesu diṭṭhe diṭṭhamattaṃ bhavissati, sute sutamattaṃ bhavissati, mute mutamattaṃ bhavissati, viññāte viññātamattaṃ bhavissati. "
msgstr "“In that case, when it comes to things that are to be seen, heard, thought, and known: in the seen will be merely the seen; in the heard will be merely the heard; in the thought will be merely the thought; in the known will be merely the known. "

msgctxt "sn35.95:10.2"
msgid "Yato kho te, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhasutamutaviññātabbesu dhammesu diṭṭhe diṭṭhamattaṃ bhavissati, sute sutamattaṃ bhavissati, mute mutamattaṃ bhavissati, viññāte viññātamattaṃ bhavissati; "
msgstr "When this is the case, "

msgctxt "sn35.95:10.3"
msgid "tato tvaṃ, mālukyaputta, na tena. "
msgstr "you won’t be ‘by that’. "

msgctxt "sn35.95:10.4"
msgid "Yato tvaṃ, mālukyaputta, na tena; "
msgstr "When you’re not ‘by that’, "

msgctxt "sn35.95:10.5"
msgid "tato tvaṃ, mālukyaputta, na tattha. "
msgstr "you won’t be ‘in that’. "

msgctxt "sn35.95:10.6"
msgid "Yato tvaṃ, mālukyaputta, na tattha; "
msgstr "When you’re not ‘in that’, "

msgctxt "sn35.95:10.7"
msgid "tato tvaṃ, mālukyaputta, nevidha, na huraṃ, na ubhayamantarena. "
msgstr "you won’t be in this world or the world beyond or in between the two. "

msgctxt "sn35.95:10.8"
msgid "Esevanto dukkhassā”ti. "
msgstr "Just this is the end of suffering.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn35.95:11.1"
msgid "“Imassa khvāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi: "
msgstr "“This is how I understand the detailed meaning of the Buddha’s brief statement: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
